{"id":2518,"date":"2021-11-26T17:16:19","date_gmt":"2021-11-26T17:16:19","guid":{"rendered":"https:\/\/d-themes.com\/wordpress\/udesign\/documentation\/?p=2518"},"modified":"2022-01-05T18:04:59","modified_gmt":"2022-01-05T18:04:59","slug":"post-types-unlimited","status":"publish","type":"post","link":"https:\/\/d-themes.com\/wordpress\/udesign\/documentation\/2021\/11\/26\/post-types-unlimited\/","title":{"rendered":"Post Types Unlimited"},"content":{"rendered":"\n<p>Post Types Unlimited plugin provides full functionalities to add or manage various kinds of post types and appropriate taxonomies.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>For Example: Building a Real Estate Site.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>First, a post type is needed which is capable of property management. How to create a property post type using <strong>Post Types Unlimited<\/strong> is the same as follows.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<ol><li>Activate <strong>Post Types Unlimited<\/strong> plugin and then you can see <strong>Post Types<\/strong> item at the WP Admin Sidebar. Go to&nbsp;<strong>Post Types<\/strong>&nbsp;and click&nbsp;<strong>Add New&nbsp;<\/strong>Button to add a new custom post type.<\/li><\/ol>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-full\"><img width=\"930\" height=\"442\" src=\"https:\/\/d-themes.com\/wordpress\/udesign\/documentation\/wp-content\/uploads\/sites\/17\/2021\/11\/compatible-plugin-port-type-2.jpg\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-3984\" srcset=\"https:\/\/d-themes.com\/wordpress\/udesign\/documentation\/wp-content\/uploads\/sites\/17\/2021\/11\/compatible-plugin-port-type-2.jpg 930w, https:\/\/d-themes.com\/wordpress\/udesign\/documentation\/wp-content\/uploads\/sites\/17\/2021\/11\/compatible-plugin-port-type-2-300x143.jpg 300w, https:\/\/d-themes.com\/wordpress\/udesign\/documentation\/wp-content\/uploads\/sites\/17\/2021\/11\/compatible-plugin-port-type-2-768x365.jpg 768w, https:\/\/d-themes.com\/wordpress\/udesign\/documentation\/wp-content\/uploads\/sites\/17\/2021\/11\/compatible-plugin-port-type-2-150x71.jpg 150w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 930px) 100vw, 930px\" \/><figcaption>Add a new post type<\/figcaption><\/figure>\n\n\n\n<ol><li><\/li><li>Input data of custom post type and click&nbsp;<strong>publish<\/strong>&nbsp;button, then you can see a new item at the left menu named your custom post type\u2019s name.<\/li><\/ol>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-full\"><img width=\"930\" height=\"442\" src=\"https:\/\/d-themes.com\/wordpress\/udesign\/documentation\/wp-content\/uploads\/sites\/17\/2021\/11\/compatible-plugin-port-type-3.jpg\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-3983\" srcset=\"https:\/\/d-themes.com\/wordpress\/udesign\/documentation\/wp-content\/uploads\/sites\/17\/2021\/11\/compatible-plugin-port-type-3.jpg 930w, https:\/\/d-themes.com\/wordpress\/udesign\/documentation\/wp-content\/uploads\/sites\/17\/2021\/11\/compatible-plugin-port-type-3-300x143.jpg 300w, https:\/\/d-themes.com\/wordpress\/udesign\/documentation\/wp-content\/uploads\/sites\/17\/2021\/11\/compatible-plugin-port-type-3-768x365.jpg 768w, https:\/\/d-themes.com\/wordpress\/udesign\/documentation\/wp-content\/uploads\/sites\/17\/2021\/11\/compatible-plugin-port-type-3-150x71.jpg 150w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 930px) 100vw, 930px\" \/><figcaption>Input data of post type<\/figcaption><\/figure>\n\n\n\n<ol><li><\/li><li><\/li><li>Now You can use this post type as same as default post type.<\/li><\/ol>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-full\"><img width=\"930\" height=\"442\" src=\"https:\/\/d-themes.com\/wordpress\/udesign\/documentation\/wp-content\/uploads\/sites\/17\/2021\/11\/compatible-plugin-port-type-4.jpg\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-3986\" srcset=\"https:\/\/d-themes.com\/wordpress\/udesign\/documentation\/wp-content\/uploads\/sites\/17\/2021\/11\/compatible-plugin-port-type-4.jpg 930w, https:\/\/d-themes.com\/wordpress\/udesign\/documentation\/wp-content\/uploads\/sites\/17\/2021\/11\/compatible-plugin-port-type-4-300x143.jpg 300w, https:\/\/d-themes.com\/wordpress\/udesign\/documentation\/wp-content\/uploads\/sites\/17\/2021\/11\/compatible-plugin-port-type-4-768x365.jpg 768w, https:\/\/d-themes.com\/wordpress\/udesign\/documentation\/wp-content\/uploads\/sites\/17\/2021\/11\/compatible-plugin-port-type-4-150x71.jpg 150w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 930px) 100vw, 930px\" \/><figcaption>Properties post type<\/figcaption><\/figure>\n\n\n\n<p>Then, there are other properties needed including \u2018featured\u2019, \u2018status\u2019, \u2018city\u2019, \u2018type\u2019 which is able to be realized by taxonomies. How to add taxonomies by <strong>Post Types Unlimited<\/strong> is the same as follows.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<ol><li>Go to <strong>Post Types &gt; Taxonomies<\/strong> and click <strong>Add New<\/strong> to add a new taxonomy.<\/li><\/ol>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-full\"><img width=\"930\" height=\"442\" src=\"https:\/\/d-themes.com\/wordpress\/udesign\/documentation\/wp-content\/uploads\/sites\/17\/2021\/11\/compatible-plugin-port-type-5.jpg\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-3982\" srcset=\"https:\/\/d-themes.com\/wordpress\/udesign\/documentation\/wp-content\/uploads\/sites\/17\/2021\/11\/compatible-plugin-port-type-5.jpg 930w, https:\/\/d-themes.com\/wordpress\/udesign\/documentation\/wp-content\/uploads\/sites\/17\/2021\/11\/compatible-plugin-port-type-5-300x143.jpg 300w, https:\/\/d-themes.com\/wordpress\/udesign\/documentation\/wp-content\/uploads\/sites\/17\/2021\/11\/compatible-plugin-port-type-5-768x365.jpg 768w, https:\/\/d-themes.com\/wordpress\/udesign\/documentation\/wp-content\/uploads\/sites\/17\/2021\/11\/compatible-plugin-port-type-5-150x71.jpg 150w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 930px) 100vw, 930px\" \/><figcaption>Create a new taxonomy<\/figcaption><\/figure>\n\n\n\n<ol><li><\/li><li>Input data of the taxonomy and click <strong>publish<\/strong> button.<\/li><\/ol>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-full\"><img width=\"930\" height=\"442\" src=\"https:\/\/d-themes.com\/wordpress\/udesign\/documentation\/wp-content\/uploads\/sites\/17\/2021\/11\/compatible-plugin-port-type-6.jpg\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-3985\" srcset=\"https:\/\/d-themes.com\/wordpress\/udesign\/documentation\/wp-content\/uploads\/sites\/17\/2021\/11\/compatible-plugin-port-type-6.jpg 930w, https:\/\/d-themes.com\/wordpress\/udesign\/documentation\/wp-content\/uploads\/sites\/17\/2021\/11\/compatible-plugin-port-type-6-300x143.jpg 300w, https:\/\/d-themes.com\/wordpress\/udesign\/documentation\/wp-content\/uploads\/sites\/17\/2021\/11\/compatible-plugin-port-type-6-768x365.jpg 768w, https:\/\/d-themes.com\/wordpress\/udesign\/documentation\/wp-content\/uploads\/sites\/17\/2021\/11\/compatible-plugin-port-type-6-150x71.jpg 150w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 930px) 100vw, 930px\" \/><figcaption>Input data of a taxonomy<\/figcaption><\/figure>\n\n\n\n<p>UDesign theme provides compatibility with Post Types Unlimited plugin.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>Single page can be implemented with <a href=\"https:\/\/d-themes.com\/wordpress\/udesign\/documentation\/2021\/10\/29\/single-builder\/\">Single Builder<\/a>. Archive page can be implemented with <a href=\"https:\/\/d-themes.com\/wordpress\/udesign\/documentation\/2021\/10\/29\/archive-builder\/\">Archive Builder<\/a>. In case of making a grid type for an archive page, <a href=\"http:\/\/essential.themepunch.com\/documentation\/\">Essential Grid<\/a> plugin is recommended in UDesign. <\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>Now, We can create contents of single and archive pages and then set the layout of them using <a href=\"https:\/\/d-themes.com\/wordpress\/udesign\/documentation\/2021\/10\/24\/what-is-udesign-layout-builder\/\">Layout Builder<\/a> as following image.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><img width=\"1024\" height=\"488\" src=\"https:\/\/d-themes.com\/wordpress\/udesign\/documentation\/wp-content\/uploads\/sites\/17\/2021\/11\/compatible-plugin-port-type-7-1024x488.jpg\" alt=\"Compatible-Plugin-Port-Type\" class=\"wp-image-3645\" srcset=\"https:\/\/d-themes.com\/wordpress\/udesign\/documenta